# UI Standards

## Purpose
Keep front-end code accessible, maintainable, and visually consistent.

## Requirements
- use semantic HTML first
- maintain keyboard accessibility and sensible focus behavior
- support loading, empty, success, and error states
- keep components focused and reusable
- separate tokens/styles from component behavior where possible
- prefer maintainable CSS architecture over ad hoc overrides
- keep client-side state scoped as tightly as possible
- ensure responsive behavior for common viewport sizes
- avoid visual drift from the design system

## Apply When
- building components
- debugging layout or interaction issues
- translating design artifacts into code
